OOPS :- object oriented programing system is a machanism for software devlopment. By using OOPS we can make more secure , reliable software application . It Enhance the security and reusability.

There are classes and objects____

Pillers of OOPS : -
    1. Encapsulation 
    2. Inheritance 
    3. Polymorphism 
    4. Abstraction 

class : Class is collection of Data Member And member function. Class is a blue print of object.
Object : Object is an instance of a class . It has method and properties which were defined in the class.
memory is allocated to bjects as it is created.

Static variable --- class variables 
Non Static variable -- Object -- instance Variables

